# Mapbox Best Practices Reference

This document contains comprehensive best practices, code patterns, and implementation examples for Mapbox development. Reference this when implementing complex features or debugging issues.

## Table of Contents
1. [Map Initialization Patterns](#map-initialization-patterns)
2. [Source and Layer Management](#source-and-layer-management)
3. [Performance Optimization](#performance-optimization)
4. [Event Handling](#event-handling)
5. [Mobile Implementation](#mobile-implementation)
6. [Error Handling](#error-handling)
7. [Accessibility](#accessibility)
8. [Security](#security)
9. [Data Integration Patterns](#data-integration-patterns)

## Map Initialization Patterns

### Always Wait for Map Load
```javascript
//  BAD: Adding layers immediately
const map = new mapboxgl.Map({...});
map.addLayer({...}); // May fail

//  GOOD: Wait for load event
const map = new mapboxgl.Map({...});
map.on('load', () => {
  map.addLayer({...});
});
React Lifecycle Management
javascript//  BEST: Proper React integration
import { useEffect, useRef } from 'react';

function MapComponent() {
  const mapContainer = useRef(null);
  const map = useRef(null);

  useEffect(() => {
    if (map.current) return; // Initialize only once

    map.current = new mapboxgl.Map({
      container: mapContainer.current,
      style: 'mapbox://styles/mapbox/streets-v12',
      center: [-74.5, 40],
      zoom: 9
    });

    map.current.on('load', () => {
      // Safe to add layers and sources
    });

    return () => map.current.remove(); // Cleanup
  }, []);

  return <div ref={mapContainer} style={{ width: '100%', height: '100%' }} />;
}
Source and Layer Management
Defensive Programming Pattern
javascriptfunction addLayerSafely(map, layer) {
  // Check and remove existing layer
  if (map.getLayer(layer.id)) {
    map.removeLayer(layer.id);
  }

  // Check and remove existing source if needed
  if (layer.source && typeof layer.source === 'string') {
    if (map.getSource(layer.source)) {
      map.removeSource(layer.source);
    }
  }

  // Add the new layer
  map.addLayer(layer);
}
Batch Updates for Performance
javascriptfunction updateMultipleLayers(map, updates) {
  map.once('idle', () => {
    updates.forEach(update => {
      const layer = map.getLayer(update.id);
      if (layer) {
        Object.entries(update.paint || {}).forEach(([key, value]) => {
          map.setPaintProperty(update.id, key, value);
        });
      }
    });
  });
}
