## Performance Optimization for Large Datasets

### Performance Concerns with 16+ Layers

With up to 16 large GeoJSON layers rendering simultaneously, performance optimization becomes critical. Here are the key strategies and solutions:

### Performance Limits and Thresholds

| Feature Count | Performance | Strategy |
|---------------|-------------|----------|
| < 10,000 total | Excellent (60 FPS) | Standard implementation |
| 10,000 - 25,000 | Good (45+ FPS) | Add viewport filtering |
| 25,000 - 50,000 | Manageable (30+ FPS) | Enable clustering + LOD |
| 50,000+ | Consider alternatives | Vector tiles or deck.gl |

### Core Optimization Strategies

#### 1. Viewport-Based Feature Filtering
```typescript
class ViewportFeatureManager {
  filterFeaturesByViewport(features: GeoJSON.Feature[], bounds: LngLatBounds): GeoJSON.Feature[] {
    return features.filter(feature => {
      if (feature.geometry.type === 'Point') {
        const [lng, lat] = feature.geometry.coordinates;
        return bounds.contains([lng, lat]);
      }
      return true;
    });
  }

  // Reduces rendered features by 50-80%
  updateLayerWithViewport(layerId: string, allFeatures: GeoJSON.Feature[]) {
    const visibleFeatures = this.filterFeaturesByViewport(allFeatures, this.getCurrentBounds());
    this.updateLayer(layerId, { type: 'FeatureCollection', features: visibleFeatures });
  }
}
```

#### 2. Level of Detail (LOD) Management
```typescript
class LODManager {
  simplifyFeatures(features: GeoJSON.Feature[], zoom: number): GeoJSON.Feature[] {
    const tolerance = this.getToleranceForZoom(zoom);

    return features.map(feature => {
      if (feature.geometry.type === 'LineString' || feature.geometry.type === 'Polygon') {
        // Simplify geometry based on zoom level
        return {
          ...feature,
          geometry: simplify(feature.geometry, tolerance)
        };
      }
      return feature;
    });
  }

  private getToleranceForZoom(zoom: number): number {
    // Higher tolerance (more simplification) at lower zoom levels
    return Math.max(0.0001, 0.01 / Math.pow(2, zoom - 10));
  }
}
```

#### 3. Smart Clustering Configuration
```typescript
const getClusterConfig = (zoom: number, featureCount: number) => {
  if (featureCount < 1000) return null; // No clustering needed

  return {
    cluster: true,
    clusterMaxZoom: zoom < 8 ? 12 : 16,
    clusterRadius: zoom < 8 ? 80 : 40,
    clusterMinPoints: zoom < 8 ? 5 : 2
  };
};
```

#### 4. Automatic Quality Management
```typescript
class QualityManager {
  private performanceMode: 'auto' | 'high' | 'medium' | 'low' = 'auto';

  adjustQualityBasedOnPerformance(currentFPS: number, featureCount: number) {
    if (this.performanceMode !== 'auto') return;

    if (currentFPS < 30) {
      this.degradeQuality();
    } else if (currentFPS > 50 && featureCount < 20000) {
      this.improveQuality();
    }
  }

  private degradeQuality() {
    // Reduce feature density, increase clustering, simplify geometry
    this.currentSettings = {
      maxFeaturesPerLayer: Math.max(1000, this.currentSettings.maxFeaturesPerLayer * 0.7),
      enableClustering: true,
      simplificationTolerance: this.currentSettings.simplificationTolerance * 1.5
    };
  }
}
```

### Layer Visibility Management by Zoom
```typescript
const LAYER_ZOOM_CONFIG = {
  'satellite-base': { minZoom: 0, maxZoom: 22 },
  'state-boundaries': { minZoom: 0, maxZoom: 10 },
  'county-boundaries': { minZoom: 8, maxZoom: 22 },
  'public-hunts': { minZoom: 6, maxZoom: 22 },
  'detailed-trails': { minZoom: 12, maxZoom: 22 }
};

class LayerVisibilityManager {
  updateLayerVisibilityForZoom(zoom: number) {
    Object.entries(LAYER_ZOOM_CONFIG).forEach(([layerId, config]) => {
      const visible = zoom >= config.minZoom && zoom <= config.maxZoom;
      this.setLayerVisibility(layerId, visible);
    });
  }
}
```

### Performance Monitoring Implementation
```typescript
class PerformanceMonitor {
  private metrics = {
    fps: 0,
    renderTime: 0,
    memoryUsage: 0,
    featureCount: 0
  };

  startMonitoring() {
    setInterval(() => {
      this.metrics.fps = this.calculateFPS();
      this.metrics.memoryUsage = this.getMemoryUsage();
      this.metrics.featureCount = this.getTotalFeatureCount();

      this.checkPerformanceThresholds();
    }, 1000);
  }

  private checkPerformanceThresholds() {
    if (this.metrics.fps < 30) {
      console.warn('Low FPS detected:', this.metrics.fps);
      this.triggerQualityDegradation();
    }

    if (this.metrics.memoryUsage > 200) {
      console.warn('High memory usage:', this.metrics.memoryUsage, 'MB');
      this.triggerMemoryCleanup();
    }
  }
}
```

### Alternative High-Performance Solutions

#### When to Use Vector Tiles
- **Threshold**: Total features exceed 50,000 across all layers
- **Benefits**: Server-side filtering, infinite scalability
- **Implementation**: Convert PostGIS data to vector tiles using `tippecanoe`

#### When to Use deck.gl
- **Threshold**: Single layer has >100,000 features or need advanced visualizations
- **Benefits**: GPU-accelerated rendering, 3D capabilities
- **Trade-offs**: Additional complexity, larger bundle size

```typescript
// deck.gl integration example for extremely large datasets
import { Deck } from '@deck.gl/core';
import { GeoJsonLayer } from '@deck.gl/layers';

const deckInstance = new Deck({
  canvas: 'deck-canvas',
  layers: [
    new GeoJsonLayer({
      id: 'large-hunt-data',
      data: '/api/layers/all-hunts-optimized',
      getFillColor: [255, 140, 0],
      getLineColor: [255, 255, 255],
      lineWidthMinPixels: 1
    })
  ]
});
```

### Memory Management Strategies

```typescript
class MemoryManager {
  private featureCache = new Map<string, GeoJSON.FeatureCollection>();

  cleanupInvisibleLayers() {
    // Remove data for layers outside viewport or zoom range
    this.featureCache.forEach((data, layerId) => {
      if (!this.isLayerVisible(layerId)) {
        this.featureCache.delete(layerId);
      }
    });
  }

  limitFeatureProperties(features: GeoJSON.Feature[]): GeoJSON.Feature[] {
    // Remove unnecessary properties to reduce memory
    return features.map(feature => ({
      ...feature,
      properties: {
        id: feature.properties?.id,
        name: feature.properties?.name,
        // Only keep essential properties
      }
    }));
  }
}
```

### Complete Optimized Implementation

```typescript
// OptimizedProgrammaticMap.tsx - Production-ready component
export const OptimizedProgrammaticMap: React.FC<MapProps> = ({ layers }) => {
  const mapRef = useRef<mapboxgl.Map>();
  const [performanceMetrics, setPerformanceMetrics] = useState({
    fps: 60,
    featureCount: 0,
    memoryUsage: 0
  });

  const optimizer = useMemo(() => new MapPerformanceOptimizer(), []);

  useEffect(() => {
    if (mapRef.current) {
      optimizer.initialize(mapRef.current);
